author: CNN
description:
Negotiators from the US and China have signaled progress on trade talks between the global powers, with US Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent touting the “substantial framework” of a deal to avoid escalating tariffs. But US officials have indicated that the future of a potential trade deal will ultimately hinge on this week’s meeting between US President Donald Trump and Chinese leader Xi Jinping.

Fredricka Whitfield speaks with CNN global affairs analyst Kimberly Dozier.  #CNN #News
title: US and Chinese officials reach 'framework' of a trade deal

author: CNN
description: CNN's Fredricka Whitfield speaks with House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries (D-NY) about the government shutdown, his endorsement of Zohran Mamdani, healthcare costs, the demolition of the East Wing of the White House, and other topics. #CNN #News
title: One-on-one with House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries

author: CNN
description: A recent Pew survey found that a median of 58% of adults in 23 countries are dissatisfied with how their democracy works, and 60% of the US shares that view. CNN's Fareed Zakaria observes that "today's challenge is moral, not managerial. . .When citizens no longer trust the referees, they stop obeying the rules. Every election becomes a civil war by other means. Truth itself becomes tribal. We have entered democracy's post-referee age." #CNN #News
title: Fareed's Take: Democracy's crisis of faith

author: CNN
description: Zohran Mamdani, the Democratic nominee for New York City mayor, spoke to CNN's Gloria Pazmino about how he plans to fight — and, when possible, work with — President Donald Trump's administration as mayor of America's biggest city. #cnn #zohranmamdani #newyorkcity #mayor #trump
title: Mamdani on Trump: I am prepared to 'take this administration to court' as mayor

author: CNN
description:
Rev. Jesse Jackson Sr., a civil rights leader and political outsider, ran for president in two groundbreaking campaigns that changed American politics.

Jake Tapper speaks with CNN anchor Abby Phillip about her new book "A Dream Deferred: Jesse Jackson and the Fight for Black Political Power." #CNN #News
title: How Jesse Jackson ushered in a new era of American politics

author: CNN
description: JoJo Siwa has grown up in public. From her compelling reality TV debut at nine years old to her more recent stint on the UK's "Celebrity Big Brother," the pop star and dancer has entertained, confused and even angered fans over the years -- all while making millions in the process. Now, still only 22, she says she's embarking on a new chapter. CNN's Scottie Andrew met Siwa at her studio in California, watching a rehearsal for her new tour and discussing her evolving stardom and perspectives on sexuality. #CNN #News
title: How JoJo Siwa is evolving, from costumes to choreography

author: CNN
description:
Analysis by the Associated Press shows that Black student enrollment at elite colleges dropped this fall after steady increases over decades, and that some schools' Black enrollment was as low as 2% of incoming freshman classes.

One exception is Smith College, where the number of enrolled Black students has risen.

CNN's Victor Blackwell speaks with Joanna May, Vice President for enrollment at Smith College. #CNN #News
title: Black enrollment at many elite colleges dropped this fall

author: CNN
description:
Former California Gov. Arnold Schwarzenegger criticized congressional redistricting efforts happening across the United States during an interview with CNN's Jake Tapper. Schwarzenegger said both parties are “trying to outcheat each other” through redistricting.

#CNN #News #politics
title: Schwarzenegger blasts redistricting 'war'

author: CNN
description:
Police have arrested suspects in connection with the theft of priceless jewels from the Louvre museum, just as one attempted to leave the country, the Paris prosecutor’s office said.

CNN senior international correspondent Melissa Bell reports from Paris.

Watch the CNN FlashDoc "The Heist: The Louvre's Stolen Crown Jewels" on CNN tonight at 8pm ET/PT. #CNN #News
title: Suspects arrested over jewel theft from Louvre museum in Paris

author: CNN
description:
Former California Gov. Arnold Schwarzenegger denounced congressional redistricting efforts happening across the United States, describing them as cheating.

CNN's Jake Tapper speaks with Schwarzenegger on "State of the Union." #CNN #News
title: One-on-one with former California Gov. Arnold Schwarzenegger

author: CNN
description: Watch as CNN correspondent Isabel Rosales braves the infamous Netherworld Haunted House, transforming into a monster to scare unsuspecting guests. #cnn #news #hauntedhouse #halloween #netherworld
title: CNN correspondent goes undercover at Netherworld Haunted House

author: CNN
description:
Police have arrested suspects as part of the investigation into the theft of jewels worth tens of millions of dollars from the Louvre museum, the Paris prosecutor’s office said. CNN's Melissa Bell reports.

#CNN #News #Louvre #Paris
title: Suspects in Louvre museum heist arrested

author: CNN
description: US Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent struck an optimistic tone in Malaysia as he spoke to reporters on Sunday, after wrapping up trade talks with his Chinese counterparts. CNN's Betsy Klein discusses what this could mean for US President Donald Trump's upcoming meeting with Chinese leader Xi Jinping. #CNN #News
title: What's next for Trump-Xi trade talks

author: CNN
description: US President Donald Trump oversaw the signing of a peace accord between the leaders of Cambodia and Thailand on Sunday in Malaysia, building on a truce signed several months ago following deadly border clashes. CNN’s Ivan Watson takes a look at the key events leading up to the peace declaration, and explains what it means for Trump. #CNN #News #Cambodia #Thailand
title: Thailand and Cambodia sign peace agreement

author: CNN
description: Malaysian Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim commended US President Donald Trump for his willingness to “break some rules” to promote peace during the signing ceremony for a deal between Thailand and Cambodia, joking that the two men had a lot in common, including their respective legal woes. #CNN #News
title: 'I was in prison but you almost got there' Malaysian leader jokes to Trump

author: CNN
description: The demolition of the plant’s two 528-foot-high cooling towers marks an important step in the dismantling of the Gundremmingen nuclear power station in the southern state of Bavaria. #CNN #News #Germany
title: Germany demolishes cooling towers at nuclear power plant

author: CNN
description: The US president was met at the airport by Malaysian officials and a crowd of onlookers waving flags and dancing ahead of a summit with leaders from the ASEAN group of nations. #CNN #News
title: Trump dances on red carpet as he arrives in Malaysia

author: CNN
description:
Host Roy Wood Jr. and his panel discuss President Trump's $200 million, 90,000-square-foot ballroom plan for the East Wing of the White House, and much more on 'Have I Got News For You'. 

'Have I Got News For You' regularly airs Saturdays at 9pm ET/PT and streams on HBO Max the following day.
